StoryAsset.name: New League Match Up User Higher

keyValuePair.Value: An important win. Happy with the performance?
You've managed to open up a little gap at the top of the table with that win against your nearest challengers. It was a close game. What gave your boys the edge?
Our pressing game was excellent.

We were very combative all over the pitch. If you want to press the opposition, you have to all be in it together. We made ourselves very difficult to play through. But I think we can push on from here, though. I'm looking for a bit more creativity in future matches.
There was some great attacking play.

We know we've always got enough creative talent in the team to give us a chance in games. Credit to them, too, I can usually trust them to deliver. It was a good team performance and, whenever we needed a bit of magic, a clever pass or trick to open up space, somebody was there to make something positive happen.
It was a professional performance.

Out of possession, I think we're working very well as a unit at the moment. They boys are well-organised, they talk to each other and they're calm under pressure. It makes us a very difficult team to play against. And it gives us the confidence to really express ourselves going forward.
A draw against %1s, your nearest challengers. What did you think?
You had to settle for a draw against your nearest challengers, %1s. It leaves you still top of the table, but did the team miss an opportunity to open up a gap to the chasing pack today?
We can definitely be better than that.

It was a game our opponents really needed to win and so we weren't surprised that they did their best to put us under pressure. We looked solid enough, though. Well done to the boys for that. But, in future, I'm definitely looking for the boys to use the ball better whenever we win possession.
That's not good enough, to be honest.

Our attacking play has been great for most of the season but maybe today was a bit of an off day for the boys. We never really looked like dominating in the final third and let ourselves get physically bullied a bit by %1s. I was hoping for a win but, to be honest, we didn't do enough to deserve one here.
They'll be more disappointed than we are.

It was a decent game and it could probably have gone either way. Fair play to %1s, they got their %2s goals. But look at the table. A draw's not such a terrible result from our point of view. You'd have to say they needed the win more than we did today.
A big defeat today. Did the pressure get to your team?
It was a six-pointer today against %1s. You must be disappointed your boys slipped to a defeat. Do you think the opposition were just better on the day? Or did the pressure get to your team?
We just made too many mistakes.

We're top of the table so everybody works harder to get results against us. Why did we lose the game today? Because we gave the ball away too often and gave the opposition chances to put us under pressure. We never took control of things the way I expect us to.
We didn't support each other enough.

Overall, %1s used the ball better than us today so it was difficult for us to get control of the game. I think the difference was that we didn't get around each other to support the man in possession. We need to give our team-mate options, don't we? The boys never got going and we've paid the price.
We did okay defensively but that wasn't enough.

I'm not here to hang individual players out to dry. %1s came into this very well-prepared and very motivated. Because they dominated possession, we were under pressure for long spells in the game and, in the end, that pressure told. We needed to make much better use of the ball.
Did your team disappoint you in today's defeat?
%1s are a good team but they're below you in the table. You must have expected a better result today. What do you think went wrong for your boys?
We're not good enough to coast through games.

I'm really disappointed. The players have been fantastic recently but today our attitude let us down here. It was as if we thought we could relax and just expect chances to come our way. Well, today they didn't and we paid the price. Where was our energy when we needed it?
We need to work together as a team.

We're usually so strong as a team when it comes to supporting each other, but today we played like strangers. Each player just seemed be interested in looking after himself. We'll improve, don't worry. We'll definitely be working hard in training before the next game.
We left ourselves too exposed.

They may be below us in the table but %1s have plenty of good attacking players. They were very motivated for the win and our mistakes in possession put us under all sorts of pressure. The defeat was down to not looking after the ball properly and leaving ourselves exposed in dangerous areas.
Did you expect better from your boys today?
That draw allows the teams below you to narrow the gap. Were you a little worried your lads couldn't win? Did you expect more from them?
I want to see much more desire.

Maybe it was the pressure of a game against a highly-motivated team. The lads looked like they were happy to just wait for something to happen. I want to see them try to impose themselves more than they did today. At this level, it's about desire as much as anything.
We have to be better-focused.

The opposition were very highly-motivated today. It was a big prize on offer for them. I'm not sure our lads were able to match that desire. We weren't nearly as focused as I expect us to be. Games like this often come down to who wants it more.
It was a bad day at the office.

The positive to take from the game is that, although we didn't play well, at least we didn't lose. The boys know they weren't at their best. I know they'll be desperate to make up for it next time out.
It was a good win. What did you make of your team's performance?
You've managed to keep going at the top of the table with a good win against one of the chasing pack. How pleased were you with what you saw from your team today?
The performance was built on good defensive work.

I thought we were excellent defensively today. We looked so secure. That gave us the confidence we needed to go on and win us the game. It was a victory built on teamwork and taking responsibility in the big moments. That's what I want to see from the boys every single week now.
Every single player did his job.

We set up to win every game. For us to be successful, every player needs to do his job. That was what happened today. In possession and out of possession, every one of the boys in followed his instructions to the letter. Nobody switched off for a moment. They were great.

We set up to win every game. For us to be successful, every player needs to do his job. That was what happened today. In possession and out of possession, every one of the boys in followed his instructions to the letter. Nobody switched off for a moment. They were great.
We're really dangerous going forward.

Our attacking power makes us difficult for any defence to handle at the moment. The lads' link-up play was excellent and I was always confident that we'd have the quality to make the difference in the big moments in the game. We're definitely growing as a team.
A shattering defeat. How can you explain what happened today?
That must have looked like a routine win on paper but, instead, your team suffered a shock defeat. Nothing went right for your team. How do you explain a game like today? And how do you recover?
We just didn't get control of the game.

The opposition played above themselves today and the way they set up often gave them a man over when they were attacking. I'm disappointed our lads weren't able to find a way to counter that game plan. We need to work out how to adapt when we see ourselves getting overloaded in dangerous areas of the pitch.
We weren't well-organised defensively.

Maybe it's my imagination, but it looked to me as if my players went out there expecting an easy afternoon. The opposition were highly-motivated and aggressive. Fair play to them. We didn't really function as a unit all game and we paid a heavy price for it.
We didn't create anything going forward.

Look, it's a bad result and not a good performance. We didn't really create any worthwhile chances. And %1s are better than their position in the table suggests. But we know we can be better than we were today. We'll recover and come back stronger in our next game.
That was a disappointing result. What went wrong today?
It should have been a routine win but you were held to a draw by the bottom team in the league. Was it just a fluke result? Or did your lads let the supporters down today?
We just weren't aggressive enough.

We were too easy to play against and the opposition took advantage of that. The boys know they can't switch off in games like they did today. It's all about how we respond to a disappointing result now. We'll work the lads hard in training this week, that's for sure.
We never really looked threatening, did we?

I know our players are much, much better than they showed today. It was as if they expected chances just to fall at their feet, but they were up against a well-organised team today. Our lads didn't work hard enough to make things happen. We didn't deserve any better out of the game.
We have to support each other when we're under pressure.

Look, I don't know where to start. We made mistakes. We didn't work hard enough. We didn't look out for each other. It was always difficult for the man in possession. The fact that we were playing the team who are bottom of the %1s isn't the point. We just weren't good enough, simple as that.
Was that just a routine victory today?
Everybody expected you to win and the result was never really in doubt. What did you think was the best thing about the team's performance today?
Some of our attacking play was excellent.

The great strength of this team is that they never give up. They're persistent. They're aggressive. And they take their chances. I should be happy with the result today, I suppose. But honestly? I think we can be even better!
We've got a very honest bunch of players.

Every manager wants to be able to rely on his players. Whether we're playing a team at the top or one like today at the bottom, I know I'll get 100% from this group of lads every game. It was another great performance, really professional. I'm delighted with them.
Sometimes the games you're expected to win are the ones that catch you out.

I thought the boys were very professional in their approach. Sometimes the games you're expected to win are the ones that catch you out. But there was never any danger of that today. We controlled things from start to finish.
You can't have been expecting that defeat. What happened?
I don't think anybody would have predicted you losing to %1s today. Do you give the opposition all the credit? Or did your boys let you down?
We definitely looked under-cooked today.

The whole point of training is to be ready and in the right frame of mind at kick-off. But the team started slowly. If anything, we looked far too casual. And that gave the opposition encouragement. You can't afford to do that against anybody at this level. We'll have to prepare better next game, for sure.
You have to match your opponent's desire.

Our opponents today were desperate for a result but they also had nothing to lose. They were quicker and more determined than us all over the pitch. I don't think we ever really got started in the game. The lads have to learn you can't turn intensity on and off like a tap.
Maybe we weren't expecting to find ourselves on the back foot.

We should have been on the front foot, taking the game to them. But, instead, we were under pressure and made some very basic errors. We had to spend far too much time trying to win back possession. The boys will learn from the experience, I'm sure. We'll be better next week, I promise you that!
You have to give the opposition credit today. Did they surprise you?
You look at the gap between the two teams in the table and a draw must seem a very poor result for your boys. Were you surprised how well the opposition played today?
We have to be more pro-active.

We were flat and the opposition were able to take advantage of that. When it's not happening for us, we always hope one of our creative players can find something extra, a bit of magic to make the difference. But that didn't happen today. We need to train harder this coming week, that's for sure.
We were just out-fought on the day.

That result came as a big surprise. Credit to the opposition. They played like they had nothing to lose. They battled hard and definitely got the better of us in every 50/50. They fought harder and deserved the result. We just weren't at it today.

That result came as a big surprise. Credit to the opposition. They played like they had nothing to lose. They battled hard and definitely got the better of us in every 50/50. They fought harder and deserved the result. We just weren't at it today.
I think we got ourselves ambushed today.

Maybe our opposition scouting wasn't as good as it usually is. We seemed surprised by their energy and their quality. We didn't adapt to deal with their runs in behind. Honestly? They were better than we expected them to be. We have to learn lessons from that and prepare better in future.
How comfortable was that win today?
The win keeps you top and it all but confirms %1s's relegation. How do you feel about sealing their fate today?
The lads just got the job done.

We have to approach every game with the same attitude. We're top and, if we want to stay there, we have to keep winning. That's the mind-set I want from my players. The boys just got on with it and turned in a very professional display.
We weren't in the mood to go easy on anyone.

I don't want to sound heartless but the opposing team aren't my problem. I just want my lads to go out and win games, whoever we're up against. My players were absolutely ruthless today and that's exactly what I want from them. We've got our own job to do here.
Our job is just to win games.
All I'm concerned about is how we play and whether we get the right results. I can't afford to worry about what a game means to our opponents. We were professional today and got the job done.
All I'm concerned about is how we play and whether we get the right results. I can't afford to worry about what a game means to our opponents. We were professional today and got the job done.
It's so tight in the table. Was this a significant defeat?
%1s are just behind you in the table and were desperate for a result to put pressure on you. You must be disappointed to lose. Was the problem you couldn't match their intensity?
We got a bit overwhelmed.

In a game like today, between closely-matched teams, it's about winning the battles in the key areas. We weren't good enough. We weren't up for the fight and our players let themselves be dominated all over the pitch. We ended up a bit overwhelmed, to be honest.
We just didn't cope when we were under pressure.

We got exposed too often defensively. We were put under pressure for long spells and our lads just couldn't deal with that. I'm not sure if it's physical or psychological. Either way, the boys have to work harder, train harder and be better prepared for times in games when the other team's on top.
We never threatened going forward.

It's difficult to put consistent pressure on the opposition when, for whatever reason, your players can't ever get full control of the game. That's what happened to us today. We just didn't get enough of the ball. It was all a bit too easy for %1s.
Were you disappointed with a draw?
It was always likely to be a close game. Are you satisfied with a draw or do you think you missed an opportunity to get clear of one of the teams chasing you in the table?
We need better focus.

I think the lads know they let themselves down today. It's not enough to play well for 89 minutes and then get sloppy when it really matters. That's what costs you the game. We should have won, shouldn't we? That's an opportunity missed.
You can't take your foot off the gas.

Too many of our players were sort of in and out of the game today. It's not enough to be committed for spells during a match but then to allow your intensity to drop. The lads have to realise we should be pushing for more goals from first minute to last.
I can't fault our commitment.

I think the lads probably deserved better from the game. We worked hard and, for spells, we were more than a match for the opposition. I don't know if it was a bit of fatigue or just letting our concentration slip but, as soon as we dropped off our game a little, we were made to pay.
Were you happy with the performance today?
That was a close-run thing but your players found enough to win the game. What made the difference for your boys today?
We battled as a team.

I thought we were outstanding defensively today. We put pressure on the man in possession and made sure we blocked off the spaces around our box. That's the kind of organised and committed performance I want to see every week. We looked hungry!
We had real togetherness.

I thought the lads were outstanding today. They won their individual battles as we hoped they would. What was really impressive, though, was how they worked together as a team, supporting and covering for each other. There was always an option for the man on the ball.

I thought the lads were outstanding today. They won their individual battles as we hoped they would. What was really impressive, though, was how they worked together as a team, supporting and covering for each other. There was always an option for the man on the ball.
Our link-up play was excellent.

Yes, I was pretty pleased with how we performed today. The players worked hard for each other and that made life very difficult for the opposition. We looked the better team all-round. The victory was definitely deserved.
Happy with the win today?
That was a real test for your boys today. And they passed with flying colours. You must be happy with the win and happy with your team's performance?
We've got lads who make a difference.

We really took the game to the opposition today. The lads were always willing to chase lost causes. We played some decent football. And we took our chances when they came. I'm happy. And I'll be even happier if I see that energy from the boys every week!
That was a professional performance.

We talked before the game about how important it was for us to play the game at our pace. The boys went out and did that today. We dominated the game for long spells and always looked in good control. The result was reward for the display. We definitely deserved the win.
We took charge of situations.

I thought the lads turned in a very convincing and mature display today. They kept their discipline, stayed calm when we were under pressure and used the ball well, too. That steadiness gave us a solid base to work from. We played with real authority.
So, a draw against %1s in a very close game. Are you satisfied?
Yourselves and %1s are pretty evenly matched, it seems. Were you satisfied with a draw from today's game? Was it a fair result?
We could have created more.

Look, the lads were very determined today. They didn't shirk a tackle all afternoon. But maybe we needed to see a little more creativity from them. If we'd been able to find the right pass once or twice, maybe got an extra man in the box, that draw could easily have turned into a win.
We let ourselves down defensively.

I know they were up against good players today. %1s are a good team. But we didn't dominate the game like I know we can. Whenever we lost possession we looked a bit rattled, didn't we? We made too many mistakes defensively and, ultimately, those mistakes are why we had to settle for the draw.
A draw was about right.

%1s are a good side going forward. You don't need me pointing that out after their %2s goals today. We had to spend quite a lot of our time scrapping for possession and trying to stop them playing. All in all, you could say it was a game neither side did enough in to win.
That could prove a costly defeat. Are you unhappy with your team?
%1s and yourselves are so closely-matched. This might mean the defeat is even more disappointing for you. Where did it go wrong for your boys?
We've mugged ourselves again!

We've looked really solid defensively the last few matches. I don't know what happened. Today we played like we'd never met each other before. I can't explain it. But, for sure, I know we'll be working very hard with them as a unit in training this week.
We looked toothless today.

We were up against a good %1s team today. The lads were under pressure for long periods and that meant we couldn't get numbers forward often enough. So, it made for a tough day for us. We just didn't create enough chances to deserve anything from the game.
We competed but it wasn't enough.

On the day, I think you'd have to say we were beaten by a better team. But I'm not going to have a pop at the lads about the defeat. They battled well against a good %1s side. We tried to get some decent possession. But individual errors meant all the hard work went to waste. Football can be tough sometimes.
That wasn't the result we expected. What happened?
I don't think many people expected %1s to come out on top in this game. Were you as surprised as the rest of us? Why were your boys second-best today?
You can't make those simple mistakes.

I thought the opposition set up very well against us and we just played into their hands too often. The boys are professional enough to know what they did wrong. They'll take responsibility for those individual errors. They'll come into training now determined to put things right before our next game.
Did we expect an easy game?

I warned the boys that the opposition are a better side than people think. Maybe the lads missed that part of the team talk. That's what it looked like. They were never aggressive enough. You have to make things happen in games. Chances don't just get handed to you on a plate.
We'll put things right, I promise.

I trust my players. They always try to be professional about their work. So I shouldn't need to remind them of the mistakes they made today. We were nowhere near good enough. We'll be in for extra training and we'll make sure we put things right before our next game.
Credit the opposition or criticise your own team?
Looking at form and league positions, this must have been a game you expected to win not draw. Was it a case of the opposition playing above themselves or your team being below par?
Where was the energy?

Of course I'm disappointed to only draw today. I wanted to see a lot more energy all over the pitch. Where was our hunger? We didn't put them under pressure often enough, that's for sure. I think if we'd been more aggressive that's a game we would have won.
We were flat today.

Playing with energy, playing on the front foot. That's what's seen us get some decent results lately. So I don't know what happened today. We were slow to react in dangerous situations. We didn't take the game to our opponents. The boys need to sharpen up or I'll have to look at making changes.
We ended up hanging on a bit.

Of course I'm not happy with the draw today. I expected us to win. But it could have been even worse. If it hadn't been for one or two last-ditch tackles, I could have been standing here talking about a defeat. I'm not happy and the boys aren't either. They know when they've come up short.
A routine win today. Are you satisfied?
Are you satisfied with the win today? And how do you feel about your victory pretty much condemning %1s to relegation now?
I respect my players' professionalism.

To be honest, there's no room for sentiment at this stage of the season. We have to look after our own business and the boys did that today. If we can be as professional as that in our work in future games, I'll be happy.
We want to be consistent.

It doesn't matter who we play or what the result means to the opposition, I know what I'll get from my players. They are very professional in their attitude. They never seem to let themselves or the fans down. And they did a very good job again today.
Sometimes you have to be patient.

There was a lot at stake for the opposition today, of course. They were fighting for their lives and so that made it difficult for us. They tried to stop us playing but the lads kept going and got their rewards eventually. We needed the win so I'm very pleased.
